HELLO IM BACK FROM A LOOOONG BREAK
==================

Changes:
------------------

- back to 16 Playerspawns from 32 reasons below
- Fixed a Bug where people couldnt place a Bomb anymore
- simpler area dmg detectors (boxes instead of balls > better performance)
- throw distance increased

### Reason why 16 players only:

Since someone said that it crashes the server i think that its to heavy with 32 Players throwing bombs at the same time since a Bomberman game is usually played with 4 Players only not 32!!
The second reason is the entity limit. with 32 Players the limit was almost reached. Now if there are some server side entitys added they surpass 2048 and crash the game

I moved it to Other/misc section because its clearly not a minigame
If this map is stable without bugs i will make more bomberman maps


How to play
------------------

Aim is to kill the enemy team
With E you throw bombs
When looking on the ground while pressing E
you lay a bomb
You can kick a layed bomb by running towards the bomb
There are boxes that can be broken to aquire amazing power ups

Power ups
------------------

- Extrabomb.......you can lay 1 more bomb at same time
- Firepower.......Aoe radius increases
- Health..........You get 25 hp
- Superhealth.....Full heal and HP cap to 150
- Speed...........you run faster

### Bomb Types

- Icebomb..........Slows
- Firebomb.........Molotov Coctail
- Electrobomb......Stuns
- Windbomb.........Throws you in the air  **REMOVED**

After 3 minutes of gametime sudden death starts
which cause the lava to rise

- 16 CT Spawns
- 16 T Spawns

Current Bugs Statement
------------------

##### Players unable to lay a bomb
FIXED!!!!

Great fun to play at either LAN parties or with people you don't even know. Two bunkers face each other in the middle of a suburban area, on one side of the playing field, you have a small building with an alleyway in the middle.

In the middle, a sewage pipe with a special AWP care package, on the other side, a small road and a train wreck. All the while, filled with obstacles such as cars, rocks, vending machines, and even *gasp* landmines! Watch out for those buggers, they'll take you out if you step on em.

A sewer system connects each base with the pipe in the middle, which provides some intense close combat fights. Depending on your spawn point, you will recieve certain weapons upon spawning. However, if you don't like the weapon you are given, you can buy your own choice.
Set the server's pushscale limit to 4000 (phys_pushscale 4000) for this map to work...have fun :)

bk_castle_v3
(Breakable_castle_v3)


     The idea of the map was taken from other break floor, or break ceiling, or break wall maps, except i wanted it to be somewhat original in the design.  i thought it would always be cool if you could have a battle with destroyable castles, so i decided to map a small version of one.

MAP DESIGN:

     The map design is T and CT start on opposite ends of a rectangular map. Both teams start in little underground spawn areas. (Built to provide time to purchase weapons, so you don't get slaughtered instantly) Once you are ready, you will leave this underground part, and be in the middle of your castle, which the entrance will have a moat and a bridge of course. In the middle of the map will be a small bunker, to provide a little protection getting to the enemy castle. There is also a little underground part below the bunker, 4 entrances, not the greatest advantage point, but can be useful somewhat. The entrances are breakable parts of the ground, and the gibs are ceiling tile, remember that this is the beta.

PLEASE NOTE -----------------------------------------------------
           |           BOTS DO NOT WORK ON THIS MAP.             |
            -----------------------------------------------------

EDIT: Skybox and the details of the map are lacking, near future if people wants better updates, i can improve the fog, skybox, and layout of the map.

You're NOT allowed to change any parts of this map or use any parts of this map on other maps.

--------------------------------------------

My 4th CS:S map. It works as a main menu's dynamic background, like in HL2 for example. It replaces the default static background image with a special Zombie Escape themed map.

Content:

- Custom loading screen;
- Background map that contains 2 random rooms;
- Music in each random room that can be adjusted in Options > Sound > Music Volume.

--------------------------------------------

Installation

- Download the bg zombie escape.rar archive;
- Unpack it's content into your CSS/cstrike/custom folder. **IMPORTANT**: You must keep the folders hierarchy exactly the same as in the archive (for example, the materials folder should be in "CSS/cstrike/custom/_bg zombie escape/materials");


**IMPORTANT**:

The map is using a custom autoexec.cfg file which contains console commands needed for the map to work. If you're already using your own autoexec.cfg, delete the new one and add next strings to your file:

	map_background bg_zombie_escape			// enabling the map as the background
	mat_colorcorrection 1					// enabling color correction for better look of the map (optional, but recommended)

--------------------------------------------

De-installation

If for whatever reason you don't want this map to stay as the background anymore, just delete your "CSS/cstrike/custom/_bg zombie escape" folder. If you are using your own autoexec.cfg file, also delete the strings listed above from it. 

--------------------------------------------

Notes

- Since the map itself takes much more disc space than a single simple default background image, it makes the game to launch much longer.
- The map sets "mp_autokick" parameter to 0, since without it the map will keep closing after about 3-4 minutes and changing to the loading screen image without any warning.

--------------------------------------------

Beta

The map is in beta right now. I'm planning to add one more random room to it.
I'll add a short preview video soon for these who don't want to download a huge 11 MB archive without knowing what's in it.

--------------------------------------------

--------------------_**UPDATE**_--------------------

I forgot to include the color correction file. It's fixed now, so people who have already downloaded the map should redownload it again to see the map the way it's supposed to be. Thanks.
